## Goal

After Keycloak token exchange:

1. parse the token
2. extract the user identifier
3. call `Lancelot.getUserById(...)`
4. build the Arthur session from Lancelot data

---

## 1. Update `handleCallback()`

Use the token response, extract `id_token`, parse claims, then call Lancelot.

```java
@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
@Slf4j
public class AuthService {

    private final WebClient webClient;
    private final RedisAuthTransactionService redisAuthTransactionService;
    private final LancelotClient lancelotClient;
    private final OidcDiscoveryClient oidcDiscoveryClient;
    private final JwtService jwtService;
    private final RedisSessionService redisSessionService;

    public void handleCallback(String code, String state) {
        AuthTransaction tx = redisAuthTransactionService.findByState(state);
        if (tx == null) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("Invalid or expired state");
        }

        AppConfigResponse appConfig = lancelotClient.getApp(tx.getAppId());

        OidcMetadata metadata = oidcDiscoveryClient.loadMetadata(appConfig.getIssuerUri());

        String tokenUrl = toInternalUrl(metadata.getTokenEndpoint());

        Map<String, Object> tokenResponse = webClient.post()
                .uri(tokenUrl)
                .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)
                .body(BodyInserters.fromFormData("grant_type", "authorization_code")
                        .with("client_id", appConfig.getClientId())
                        .with("client_secret", appConfig.getClientSecret())
                        .with("code", code)
                        .with("redirect_uri", tx.getRedirectUri())
                        .with("code_verifier", tx.getCodeVerifier()))
                .retrieve()
                .onStatus(HttpStatusCode::isError, clientResponse ->
                        clientResponse.bodyToMono(String.class).flatMap(body -> {
                            log.error("Token endpoint error body: {}", body);
                            return Mono.error(new IllegalStateException("Token exchange failed: " + body));
                        }))
                .bodyToMono(new ParameterizedTypeReference<Map<String, Object>>() {})
                .block();

        log.info("Token exchange succeeded");

        String accessToken = (String) tokenResponse.get("access_token");
        String idToken = (String) tokenResponse.get("id_token");
        String refreshToken = (String) tokenResponse.get("refresh_token");

        JwtUserClaims claims = jwtService.extractClaims(idToken);

        log.info("Authenticated subject={}, username={}, email={}",
                claims.getSub(), claims.getPreferredUsername(), claims.getEmail());

        String userId = claims.getSub(); // change if Lancelot expects username/email instead

        UserResponse user = lancelotClient.getUserById(userId);

        log.info("Loaded user from Lancelot userId={}, username={}",
                user.getUserId(), user.getUsername());

        UserSession session = new UserSession();
        session.setSessionId(UUID.randomUUID().toString());
        session.setAppId(tx.getAppId());
        session.setUserId(user.getUserId());
        session.setUsername(user.getUsername());
        session.setEmail(user.getEmail());
        session.setRoles(user.getRoles());
        session.setAccessToken(accessToken);
        session.setRefreshToken(refreshToken);
        session.setCreatedAt(Instant.now());

        redisSessionService.save(session);

        redisAuthTransactionService.delete(state);

        log.info("Session created for userId={}, appId={}", user.getUserId(), tx.getAppId());
    }

    private String toInternalUrl(String url) {
        return url.replace("keycloak.kubernetes.localhost", "keycloak.ns-keycloak.svc.cluster.local");
    }
}
```

