## 2. Add a JWT parser service

For now, decode claims from `id_token`. This does **not** validate signature yet; it just parses. That is enough to move the flow forward.

```java
@Service
public class JwtService {

    public JwtUserClaims extractClaims(String jwtToken) {
        try {
            SignedJWT signedJWT = SignedJWT.parse(jwtToken);
            JWTClaimsSet claimsSet = signedJWT.getJWTClaimsSet();

            JwtUserClaims claims = new JwtUserClaims();
            claims.setSub(claimsSet.getSubject());
            claims.setPreferredUsername((String) claimsSet.getClaim("preferred_username"));
            claims.setEmail((String) claimsSet.getClaim("email"));
            claims.setGivenName((String) claimsSet.getClaim("given_name"));
            claims.setFamilyName((String) claimsSet.getClaim("family_name"));
            return claims;
        } catch (Exception e) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("Failed to parse JWT token", e);
        }
    }
}
```

