## 3. Add `LancelotClient.getUserById(...)`

If you already have this, just adapt the response type.

```java
@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
@Slf4j
public class LancelotClient {

    private final WebClient lancelotWebClient;

    public AppConfigResponse getApp(String appId) {
        return lancelotWebClient.get()
                .uri("/apps/{appId}", appId)
                .retrieve()
                .bodyToMono(AppConfigResponse.class)
                .block();
    }

    public UserResponse getUserById(String userId) {
        log.info("Calling Lancelot getUserById userId={}", userId);

        return lancelotWebClient.get()
                .uri("/users/{userId}", userId)
                .retrieve()
                .bodyToMono(UserResponse.class)
                .block();
    }
}
